# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: TheOutsidePathBegins
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah grabbed Kate's hand and let herself be pulled out of bed."
    new "Sarah grabbed Kate's hand and let herself be pulled out of bed."

    old "I trust you."
    new "I trust you."

    old "Kate threw a bag at Sarah."
    new "Kate threw a bag at Sarah."

    old "We need to move fast. Pack enough clothes to last you a few days."
    new "We need to move fast. Pack enough clothes to last you a few days."

    old "Kate quickly added."
    new "Kate quickly added."

    old "Also, grab anything of value, your jewelry, that sort of thing. We might need money along our route."
    new "Also, grab anything of value, your jewelry, that sort of thing. We might need money along our route."

    old "Sarah's heart was beating fast."
    new "Sarah's heart was beating fast."

    old "In the middle of the night, with only a few rays of moonlight for illumination, Sarah scrambled across her room, grabbing clothes and anything that had some value."
    new "In the middle of the night, with only a few rays of moonlight for illumination, Sarah scrambled across her room, grabbing clothes and anything that had some value."

    old "She stuffed them as fast into the bag Kate had given her, as she could."
    new "She stuffed them as fast into the bag Kate had given her, as she could."

    old "Sarah got dressed herself, and finally turned to Kate."
    new "Sarah got dressed herself, and finally turned to Kate."

    old "I'm ready...I think."
    new "I'm ready...I think."

    old "Kate ran up to her and grabbbed her hand. She began to pull Sarah along."
    new "Kate ran up to her and grabbbed her hand. She began to pull Sarah along."

    old "We need to keep moving."
    new "We need to keep moving."

    old "Kate pushed open the bedroom door, entering the castle hallways."
    new "Kate pushed open the bedroom door, entering the castle hallways."

    old "Sarah had never seen Kate like this, full of purpose, on a mission. She realized this might be the first time she what her friend was like as a soldier."
    new "Sarah had never seen Kate like this, full of purpose, on a mission. She realized this might be the first time she what her friend was like as a soldier."

    old "Kate never let go of Sarah's hand, guiding her along, dragging her if she felt Sarah slowed down too much."
    new "Kate never let go of Sarah's hand, guiding her along, dragging her if she felt Sarah slowed down too much."

    old "Other than Sarah and Kate, there wasn't a soul to be found. Most were still sleeping off the coronation party."
    new "Other than Sarah and Kate, there wasn't a soul to be found. Most were still sleeping off the coronation party."

    old "Eventually, Kate led Sarah down through the castle kitchen, through a side door, into the open air."
    new "Eventually, Kate led Sarah down through the castle kitchen, through a side door, into the open air."

    old "Sarah could feel the suddent shift, the cold air crawling across her skin."
    new "Sarah could feel the suddent shift, the cold air crawling across her skin."

    old "She saw some lights atop the battlements, guards patrolling the outer walls."
    new "She saw some lights atop the battlements, guards patrolling the outer walls."

    old "Kate threw a cloak over herself and pulled Sarah under it. Together they ran, through the castle gardens, towards a small cliff."
    new "Kate threw a cloak over herself and pulled Sarah under it. Together they ran, through the castle gardens, towards a small cliff."

    old "A dead end, Sarah thought. She knew every inch of the castle."
    new "A dead end, Sarah thought. She knew every inch of the castle."

    old "But Kate pulled back some brushes, revealing a hidden ladder. She dropped the ladder down and began to climb."
    new "But Kate pulled back some brushes, revealing a hidden ladder. She dropped the ladder down and began to climb."

    old "Together, using the ladder, they scaled the cliff, ending up behind one of the houses in the slum district."
    new "Together, using the ladder, they scaled the cliff, ending up behind one of the houses in the slum district."

    old "Sarah could feel a pungent smell crawling up her nostrils."
    new "Sarah could feel a pungent smell crawling up her nostrils."

    old "She hoped not to find out what it was."
    new "She hoped not to find out what it was."

    old "Kate again took Sarah's hands, and together the two ran onto the streets of the capital."
    new "Kate again took Sarah's hands, and together the two ran onto the streets of the capital."

    old "Sarah saw some people on the streets, but out here, with these cloaks, nobody knew who they were."
    new "Sarah saw some people on the streets, but out here, with these cloaks, nobody knew who they were."

    old "Kate made sure to keep up the pace, and not long after, they arrived in the harbor district."
    new "Kate made sure to keep up the pace, and not long after, they arrived in the harbor district."

    old "Hiding behind some stacked boxes, Kate turned to Sarah."
    new "Hiding behind some stacked boxes, Kate turned to Sarah."

    old "Wait here, I'll be right back."
    new "Wait here, I'll be right back."

    old "Kate ran across the harbor, ducking into one of the alleys off to the side."
    new "Kate ran across the harbor, ducking into one of the alleys off to the side."

    old "From her position, Sarah could see Kate speaking to a man. She had no idea who he was."
    new "From her position, Sarah could see Kate speaking to a man. She had no idea who he was."

    old "Only now did Sarah have a moment to consider what was going on."
    new "Only now did Sarah have a moment to consider what was going on."

    old "Had she lost her mind, she wondered."
    new "Had she lost her mind, she wondered."

    old "Here she was, away from the safety of the castle, in the dead of night, all on the word of Kate, a friend she hadn't seen in years."
    new "Here she was, away from the safety of the castle, in the dead of night, all on the word of Kate, a friend she hadn't seen in years."

    old "Sarah didn't know what to make of it, but she felt like she was doing the right thing."
    new "Sarah didn't know what to make of it, but she felt like she was doing the right thing."

    old "Not long after, Kate came running back."
    new "Not long after, Kate came running back."

    old "Come, let's go. The ship is waiting for us."
    new "Come, let's go. The ship is waiting for us."

    old "Kate reached out her hand, and instinctively, Sarah grabbed it."
    new "Kate reached out her hand, and instinctively, Sarah grabbed it."

    old "The two ran across the harbor, as fast as they could. Kate kept holding onto Sarah, making sure she kept the pace."
    new "The two ran across the harbor, as fast as they could. Kate kept holding onto Sarah, making sure she kept the pace."

    old "Following Kate, Sarah ended up on the edge of one of the piers, where a small boat was anchored."
    new "Following Kate, Sarah ended up on the edge of one of the piers, where a small boat was anchored."

    old "It read \\\"The Blunt Harpoon\\\"."
    new "It read \\\"The Blunt Harpoon\\\"."

    old "Kate climbed on board first, then pulled Sarah up behind her."
    new "Kate climbed on board first, then pulled Sarah up behind her."

    old "With Sarah safely on board, Kate runs too the helm of the ship."
    new "With Sarah safely on board, Kate runs too the helm of the ship."

    old "We're ready, captain Belmont!"
    new "We're ready, captain Belmont!"

    old "Then we set sail! Draw up the anchor!"
    new "Then we set sail! Draw up the anchor!"

    old "Sarah watched as Kate began pulling up the anchor to free the ship."
    new "Sarah watched as Kate began pulling up the anchor to free the ship."

    old "Standing at the helm she saw captain Belmont. He was late in his years, and a life spend at sea had left its marks on his face, weather-beaten as it was, making him seem even older."
    new "Standing at the helm she saw captain Belmont. He was late in his years, and a life spend at sea had left its marks on his face, weather-beaten as it was, making him seem even older."

    old "Sarah felt a jolt as the ship began to move. There was no going back, she realized, as the ship pulled from the harbor. She had made her choice."
    new "Sarah felt a jolt as the ship began to move. There was no going back, she realized, as the ship pulled from the harbor. She had made her choice."

